@startuml
title Adaptive Field Product System - Product Lifecycle

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName Monospaced

[*] --> Declared

Declared --> Forming : producer scheduled
Forming --> Current : ratified output published
Forming --> FailedPreserved : rebuild failed; prior valid kept
Forming --> Missing : formation failed; no fallback

Current --> PotentiallyStale : upstream may have changed
PotentiallyStale --> Current : validation proves still valid
PotentiallyStale --> Stale : dependency confirmed changed

Current --> Stale : invalidation record
Stale --> Forming : rebuild scheduled
Stale --> Fallback : fallback policy selected

Fallback --> Forming : higher-quality rebuild
Fallback --> Current : fallback promoted by policy
Fallback --> Missing : fallback expired / unavailable

FailedPreserved --> Forming : retry rebuild
FailedPreserved --> Stale : prior valid is now stale
FailedPreserved --> Missing : prior valid invalidated

Current --> Retired : superseded
Stale --> Retired : superseded
Fallback --> Retired : superseded
Missing --> Retired : product no longer expected

Retired --> [*]

note right of Fallback
  Fallback is explicit and diagnosable.
  Visual consumers may allow it.
  Strict consumers may reject it.
end note

note right of FailedPreserved
  Rebuild failed, but a previous
  usable product remains available
  if policy allows it.
end note

note bottom of Missing
  Missing must produce diagnostics
  when required by a consumer.
end note

@enduml
